					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12717978#post-4422847</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12717978/scp-4361#post-4422847</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 14 Nov 2019 08:34:04 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>nuhrii</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1799173</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This clearly has a lot of effort put into - the story is great and the pictures/video at the end are touching.</p> <p>However, this gets a neutral vote for me solely because I don't really think the medium the SCP is written in works - why would researchers (I suppose Markos, who now has redactional controle as project lead?) leave in all of this highly dramatic/borderline incriminating material on how they're now literally torturing SCP-4361? Even if they didn't care about that, wouldn't they consider a lot of material superfluous? I can just imagine some level 3 researcher reading this and going &quot;wait, what the fuck?&quot; This broke my suspension of disbelief, basically.</p> <p>Also, I wasn't really sufficiently sold on the characterization of Handon. Her switch from &quot;fairly laid back lead researcher on some safe skip&quot; to &quot;I discovered a deep dark secret and am willing to go rogue over this&quot; felt very quick in the grand scheme of things.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
